  "texts": [
    "To determine the number of nonsensical concepts to identify, we first compute the relative perplexity ratio (r i) for each word in the statement.",
    "As described in the methodology, this ratio reflects how much each word contributes to the overall commonsense contradiction.",
    "After calculating the r i values for all the words, we can obtain a list of r i values with length n, where n is the number of words in the statement.",
    "The top k words with the lowest r i values are then selected as the nonsensical concepts, where k represents the number of concepts we intend to identify.",
    "In this analysis, we experimented with k values of 1, 2 and 3, observing how the model's performance varied as more concepts were identified."
  ],
